This is a reopening of CONF-6232, I'll talk to Dave about it tomorrow as well. Basically this bug creates an inconsistent user experience - when you create a page, Confluence doesn't allow you to save the page untninl the greyed "New Page" has been changed to something else. When you select a template, there is a bug that ungreys the "New Page". I can't see any deliberate reason for this but I'm happy to hear an explanation. When you select a template you should be required to enter a valid page title like any other time that you create a page.

